4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ESTABLISHING REQUIREMENTS ON INSURANCE COVERAGE
5 OF CONTINUOUS GLUCOSE MONITORS AND SUPPLIES; AMENDING SECTIONS 2-18-704 AND 33-22-
6 129, MCA; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Coverage of glucose monitoring supplies. (1) Each individual
11 disability policy, certificate of insurance, and membership contract that is delivered, issued for delivery,
12 renewed, extended, or modified in this state must provide coverage of continuous glucose monitors and monitor
13 supplies if a person is diagnosed with type I or type II diabetes and a monitor is determined medically
14 necessary by the individual's health care provider and prescribed by the health care provider acting within the
15 scope of the provider's license. A policy, certificate, or contract may not contain coverage based on the stage of
16 the insured's disease of diabetes or the insured's diagnosed need for insulin.
17 (2) Coverage under this section may be subject to deductibles, coinsurance, and copayment
18 provisions. Special deductible, coinsurance, copayment, or other limitations that are not generally applicable to
19 other medical services covered under the plan may not be imposed on coverage of a continuous glucose
20 monitor.
21 (3) This section does not apply to disability income, hospital indemnity, medicare supplement,
22 specified disease, or long-term care policies.
